    layers.RandomFlip("horizontal", input_shape = (img_size,img_size,3)),
    layers.RandomRotation(0.3),
    layers.RandomZoom(0.3)
])

In[12]:
model = Sequential([
    data_augmentation,
    layers.Rescaling(1./255),
    Conv2D(16,3,padding = "same" , activation = "relu"),
    MaxPooling2D(),
    Conv2D(32,3,padding = "same" , activation = "relu"),
    MaxPooling2D(),
    Conv2D(64,3,padding = "same" , activation = "relu"),
    MaxPooling2D(),
    Dropout(0.2),
    Flatten(),
    Dense(128, activation = "relu"),
    Dense(5)
])
In[13]:
model.compile(optimizer = "adam",
              loss = tf.keras.losses.SparseCategoricalCrossentropy(from_logits = True),
              metrics = ["accuracy"])
In[14]:

In[16]:
def classify_img(image_path):
    ip_img = tf.keras.utils.load_img(image_path,target_size = (180,180))
    ip_img_arr = tf.keras.utils.img_to_array(ip_img)
    ip_img_exp_dim = tf.expand_dims(ip_img_arr,0)
    
    pred = model.predict(ip_img_exp_dim)
    result = tf.nn.softmax(pred[0])
    outcome = "The image belongs to " + Flower_name[np.argmax(result)] + " with a score of " + str(np.max(result)*100)
    return outcome
